body:
&quot;At the moment, the monster damage in W ties Kha&#039;Zix to the jungle. We&#039;d like to give him a chance to spread his wings elsewhere, so we&#039;re swapping that power for a bigger Q buff than the Duskblade changes warrant alone.&quot;

Kha&#039;zix is a jungler. He does his best work, IN THE JUNGLE. 

Next thing you know its &quot;Hmm, adc&#039;s ability scaling off ad ties them too much to bot lane, so we are gonna make all their abilities scale off magic instead&quot; or &quot;Hmm tanks are too tanky, lets make them utility supports that are squishy so they are not tied down to their role&quot; 

Now that my rant is done, a stronger Q is pretty good but that W damage was to help clear a little better in the grouped camps. Seems like riot just likes nerfing khazix in some form or other. granted his Q will be destroying people but he already did that. why not make W worth something? no one ever evolves W, let that sink in (except when they win the quest to get that final evolution)
